│ moves to the next, but it doesn't roll back the constraints added from the previous child. │
│ The fix is to save the state of the `ConstraintSystem` before iterating over the children  │
│ and restore it afterward. This ensures that each sibling subtree is analyzed with a clean  │
│ slate of constraints, inheriting only from the common parent.\n\nBy adding                 │
│ `ConstraintSystem::SaveState OnExit(CS);` before the loop that iterates over the children  │
│ of the current dominator tree node, we ensure that any modifications to the                │
│ `ConstraintSystem` `CS` within the loop (i.e., during the recursive calls to               │
│ `eliminateConstraints` for the children) are automatically undone when the `OnExit` object │
│ goes out of scope at the end of the current function's execution block. This correctly     │
│ isolates the constraints of sibling subtrees."})                                           │
