│ Based on the information provided, the bug lies in the `ConstraintElimination` pass.       │
│ Constraints from one path in the control flow graph are incorrectly applied to paths where │
│ they do not hold. This is a classic issue at control flow merge points.                    │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root cause analysis indicates that when processing sibling nodes in the dominator      │
│ tree, the constraints from the first sibling's subtree are not being rolled back before    │
│ processing the next sibling. The `ConstraintElimination` pass uses an iterative,           │
│ worklist-based approach to traverse the dominator tree, rather than a recursive one. The   │
│ logic for managing constraint scopes needs to be adjusted for this iterative structure.    │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to ensure that when the pass moves from processing one dominator tree node's    │
│ subtree to a sibling's, the constraint system is reset to the state of their common        │
│ parent. In the iterative implementation, this can be achieved by saving the state of the   │
│ `ConstraintSystem` before processing the facts and checks for a given dominator tree node, │
│ and restoring it before moving to the next one.                                            │
│                                                                                            │
│ The `WorkList` is sorted by the dominator tree DFS "in" number (`NumIn`). All              │
│ `FactOrCheck` items for the same basic block (and thus the same dominator tree node) will  │
│ have the same `NumIn`. We can detect a transition to a new node by checking if `NumIn` has │
│ changed. When it does, we restore the `ConstraintSystem` to the state it was in before     │
│ processing the previous node. The existing stack-based mechanism will then correctly       │
│ re-apply the constraints from the common dominators.                                       │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will introduce a `SaveState` object for both the signed and unsigned `ConstraintSystem`s │
│ before the main worklist loop. Then, inside the loop, I will restore the systems' states   │
│ whenever I encounter a `FactOrCheck` item belonging to a new basic block.                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ @@ -1731,7 +1731,21 @@                                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│    // Finally, process ordered worklist and eliminate implied conditions.                  │
│    SmallVector<StackEntry, 16> DFSInStack;                                                 │
│    SmallVector<ReproducerEntry> ReproducerCondStack;                                       │
│ -  for (FactOrCheck &CB : S.WorkList) {                                                    │
│ +                                                                                          │
│ +  // Save/restore the state of the constraint system when moving between sibling          │
│ +  // subtrees in the dominator tree.                                                      │
│ +  ConstraintSystem::SaveState CSSignedState(Info.getCS(true));                            │
│ +  ConstraintSystem::SaveState CSUnsignedState(Info.getCS(false));                         │
│ +  unsigned LastInNum = 0;                                                                 │
│ +                                                                                          │
│ +  for (FactOrCheck &CB : S.WorkList) {                                                    │
│ +    if (CB.NumIn != LastInNum) {                                                          │
│ +      CSSignedState.restore(Info.getCS(true));                                            │
│ +      CSUnsignedState.restore(Info.getCS(false));                                         │
│ +      LastInNum = CB.NumIn;                                                               │
│ +    }                                                                                     │
│ +                                                                                          │
│      // First, pop entries from the stack that are out-of-scope for CB. Remove             │
│      // the corresponding entry from the constraint system.                                │
│      while (!DFSInStack.empty()) {                                                         │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
