│ This is exactly the fact we're dealing with. It's coming from `ScalarEvolution`'s analysis │
│ of the loop. And it's being associated with the exit block.                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ This seems to be the source. `addInfoForInductions` is adding the fact. Let's see if it    │
│ checks for unique predecessors. It probably doesn't, because it's about loop semantics,    │
│ not simple branch conditions.                                                              │
│                                                                                            │
│ This is a much more subtle bug. The information from `ScalarEvolution` is powerful but     │
│ needs to be applied carefully. `getBackedgeTakenCount` is the number of times the backedge │
│ is taken. The condition on exit is that the IV has reached this value. This is only true   │
│ for paths exiting the loop, not all paths into the exit block.                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to apply the same logic: only add these induction-based facts if the loop exit  │
│ block has a single predecessor (the block inside the loop).                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ @@ -930,6 +930,11 @@                                                                       │
│          SmallVector<BasicBlock *> ExitingBlocks;                                          │
│          L->getExitingBlocks(ExitingBlocks);                                               │
│          for (auto *ExitingBB : ExitingBlocks) {                                           │
│ +          // The exit condition is only true on the edge from the loop. If the            │
│ +          // successor has other predecessors, we can't apply the fact to the             │
│ +          // whole successor block.                                                       │
│ +          if (!ExitBB->getUniquePredecessor())                                            │
│ +            continue;                                                                     │
│            WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                            │
│                DT.getNode(ExitBB), CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, IV, BECount));                        │
│          }                                                                                 │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│ This seems wrong. `ExitingBB` is the block *inside* the loop with the branch. We need to   │
│ check its successor, the `ExitBB`. The API is `L->getExitBlock()`. If there is a single    │
│ exit block.                                                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ Let's look at the code again.                                                              │
│ ```cpp                                                                                     │
│ // in addInfoForInductions                                                                 │
│ if (auto *ExitBB = L->getExitBlock()) {                                                    │
│   // ...                                                                                   │
│   WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                                     │
│       DT.getNode(ExitBB), CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, IV, BECount));                                 │
│ }                                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│ The `getExitBlock` returns a single block if one exists. In our case, it's `exit`.         │
│ The fix is to check `ExitBB` here.                                                         │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ @@ -926,9 +926,12 @@                                                                       │
│          // On exit, the induction variable is equal to the backedge-taken count.          │
│          // Add this as a fact to the exit block.                                          │
│          if (auto *ExitBB = L->getExitBlock()) {                                           │
│ -          WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                            │
│ -              DT.getNode(ExitBB), CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, IV, BECount));                        │
│ +          // The exit condition is only true on the edge from the loop. If the            │
│ +          // successor has other predecessors, we can't apply the fact to the             │
│ +          // whole successor block.                                                       │
│ +          if (ExitBB->getUniquePredecessor())                                             │
│ +            WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                          │
│ +                DT.getNode(ExitBB), CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, IV, BECount));                      │
│          } else {                                                                          │
│            // TODO: Handle loops with multiple exit blocks.                                │
│          }                                                                                 │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│ This looks very promising. It targets the information coming from `ScalarEvolution` and    │
│ applies the same principle of not propagating it to merge blocks.                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ Final check: `getExitBlock()` returns the single successor block outside the loop. In the  │
│ reproducer, this is `exit`. `exit->getUniquePredecessor()` will be `nullptr`. The          │
│ condition `if (ExitBB->getUniquePredecessor())` will be false, and the incorrect fact will │
│ not be added. This should fix the bug.                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ @@ -926,9 +926,12 @@                                                                       │
│          // On exit, the induction variable is equal to the backedge-taken count.          │
│          // Add this as a fact to the exit block.                                          │
│          if (auto *ExitBB = L->getExitBlock()) {                                           │
│ -          WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                            │
│ -              DT.getNode(ExitBB), CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, IV, BECount));                        │
│ +          // The exit condition is only true on the edge from the loop. If the            │
│ +          // successor has other predecessors, we can't apply the fact to the             │
│ +          // whole successor block.                                                       │
│ +          if (ExitBB->getUniquePredecessor())                                             │
│ +            WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                          │
│ +                DT.getNode(ExitBB), CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, IV, BECount));                      │
│          } else {                                                                          │
│            // TODO: Handle loops with multiple exit blocks.                                │
│          }                                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│ This seems correct and minimal.An analysis of the bug and the provided information reveals │
│ that the `ConstraintElimination` pass is incorrectly simplifying a comparison. The pass    │
│ propagates a constraint that is only true on a specific control-flow edge (from a loop to  │
│ an exit block) to the entire exit block. When this exit block is a merge point with other  │
│ predecessors, the constraint does not hold for all paths, leading to an incorrect          │
│ transformation.                                                                            │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root of the problem lies in how `ConstraintElimination` gathers facts. It uses         │
│ information from `ScalarEvolution` about loop trip counts to infer the value of induction  │
│ variables upon loop exit. Specifically, it determines that the induction variable will     │
│ equal the backedge-taken count. It then adds this equality as a fact to the loop's exit    │
│ block.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ In the provided reproducer, the loop's exit block (`exit`) has two predecessors: one from  │
│ the loop (`loop`) and one from the function entry (`entry`). The fact derived from the     │
│ loop's trip count (`n >= 1`) is only valid on the path from `loop`. However, the pass      │
│ applies it unconditionally within the `exit` block, incorrectly simplifying `icmp sgt i16  │
│ %n, 0` to `true` even for the path from `entry` where `n` can be less than 1.              │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to prevent the pass from adding these loop-derived facts to exit blocks that    │
│ are merge points. By checking if the loop's exit block has a unique predecessor, we can    │
│ ensure that such facts are only applied when they hold for all paths into the block. This  │
│ is a conservative but safe approach that prevents the incorrect transformation.            │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will modify the `addInfoForInductions` helper function in `ConstraintElimination.cpp` to │
│ add this check before creating a `ConditionFact` for a loop's exit block.                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ @@ -926,9 +926,12 @@                                                                       │
│          // On exit, the induction variable is equal to the backedge-taken count.          │
│          // Add this as a fact to the exit block.                                          │
│          if (auto *ExitBB = L->getExitBlock()) {                                           │
│ -          WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                            │
│ -              DT.getNode(ExitBB), CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, IV, BECount));                        │
│ +          // The exit condition is only true on the edge from the loop. If the            │
│ +          // successor has other predecessors, we can't apply the fact to the             │
│ +          // whole successor block.                                                       │
│ +          if (ExitBB->getUniquePredecessor())                                             │
│ +            WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                          │
│ +                DT.getNode(ExitBB), CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, IV, BECount));                      │
│          } else {                                                                          │
│            // TODO: Handle loops with multiple exit blocks.                                │
│          }                                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
