│ My previous analysis was incorrect. The logic in `addInfoForInductions` is more complex    │
│ than I thought, and the reproducer doesn't match the pattern it looks for (`if             │
│ (!match(BB.getTerminator(), m_Br(m_ICmp...))) return;`). The terminator in `loop` is `br   │
│ i1 %exitcond, label %exit, label %loop.latch`, where `%exitcond` is the `icmp`. The        │
│ terminator of the *header* (`loop`) is this branch. So it does match.                      │
│                                                                                            │
│ However, the logic I was trying to patch was this:                                         │
│ ```cpp                                                                                     │
│ // from line 1044                                                                          │
│   SmallVector<BasicBlock *> ExitBBs;                                                       │
│   L->getExitBlocks(ExitBBs);                                                               │
│   for (BasicBlock *EB : ExitBBs) {                                                         │
│     WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                                   │
│         DT.getNode(EB), CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, A, B, Precond));                                │
│   }                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│ This adds the fact `A ule B` to all exit blocks. In the reproducer, `A` is `%indvar` and   │
│ `B` is `%ext`. So it adds `%indvar ule %ext`. This is not the `eq` fact I was looking for, │
│ but it's still a fact derived from loop analysis that is being applied to a merge block.   │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to guard this with the `getUniquePredecessor` check.                            │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ @@ -1045,8 +1045,12 @@                                                                     │
│    SmallVector<BasicBlock *> ExitBBs;                                                      │
│    L->getExitBlocks(ExitBBs);                                                              │
│    for (BasicBlock *EB : ExitBBs) {                                                        │
│ -    WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                                  │
│ -        DT.getNode(EB), CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, A, B, Precond));                               │
│ +    // The exit condition is only true on the edge from the loop. If the                  │
│ +    // successor has other predecessors, we can't apply the fact to the                   │
│ +    // whole successor block.                                                             │
│ +    if (EB->getUniquePredecessor())                                                       │
│ +      WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                                │
│ +          DT.getNode(EB), CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, A, B, Precond));                             │
│    }                                                                                       │
│  }                                                                                         │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│ This seems correct and targets the exact location where facts are being added to loop exit │
│ blocks.                                                                                    │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will apply this patch.I have re-examined the code and my analysis. The issue stems from  │
│ `ConstraintElimination` not being edge-aware, causing constraints that are valid only on a │
│ specific path to be applied incorrectly at merge points in the control flow.               │
│                                                                                            │
│ My previous attempts to fix this were either based on a misinterpretation of the code or   │
│ were implemented incorrectly. The latest analysis points to the `addInfoForInductions`     │
│ function. This function analyzes loops and adds facts about the induction variable's       │
│ behavior to the loop's exit blocks. This is the source of the incorrect constraint in the  │
│ reproducer.                                                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ The function iterates through all exit blocks of a loop and adds a constraint (`%indvar    │
│ ule %ext` in the case of the reproducer) to them. It does not, however, check if these     │
│ exit blocks are merge points. If an exit block has other predecessors, this loop-derived   │
│ constraint will not hold for paths coming from those other predecessors.                   │
│                                                                                            │
│ The correct fix is to add a guard to ensure these facts are only added to exit blocks that │
│ have a single predecessor (i.e., the path from the loop is the only path into that block). │
│ This prevents the incorrect propagation of constraints to merge blocks.                    │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will modify the loop in `addInfoForInductions` that adds facts to exit blocks to include │
│ this check.                                                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp                                 │
│ @@ -1045,8 +1045,12 @@                                                                     │
│    SmallVector<BasicBlock *> ExitBBs;                                                      │
│    L->getExitBlocks(ExitBBs);                                                              │
│    for (BasicBlock *EB : ExitBBs) {                                                        │
│ -    WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                                  │
│ -        DT.getNode(EB), CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, A, B, Precond));                               │
│ +    // The exit condition is only true on the edge from the loop. If the                  │
│ +    // successor has other predecessors, we can't apply the fact to the                   │
│ +    // whole successor block.                                                             │
│ +    if (EB->getUniquePredecessor())                                                       │
│ +      WorkList.emplace_back(FactOrCheck::getConditionFact(                                │
│ +          DT.getNode(EB), CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, A, B, Precond));                             │
│    }                                                                                       │
│  }                                                                                         │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
